From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: sarun <noreply@sarun>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 18:53:53 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] brush: reset inherited call frames for shebang children

A snooped shebang child stands in for a fresh interpreter and must see its own positional arguments. Clear the caller's frames before installing the child's identity so compiler wrappers receive their real argv.

---
diff --git a/src/shell.rs b/src/shell.rs
index 72dc929..0bc731f 100644
--- a/src/shell.rs
+++ b/src/shell.rs
@@ -298,6 +298,14 @@ impl<SE: extensions::ShellExtensions> Shell<SE> {
         positional: Vec<String>,
         synth: u32,
     ) {
+        // This clone is standing in for a fresh interpreter process, not a
+        // POSIX subshell. It must not inherit the caller's script/function
+        // frames: current_shell_args() gives those frames precedence over
+        // self.args, so a shebang child invoked as `child -E ...` otherwise
+        // saw the parent's arguments (in Kbuild, the compiler wrapper saw its
+        // own pathname instead of `-E -P -x c -`). The child installs its own
+        // command-string frame immediately before execution.
+        self.call_stack = crate::callstack::CallStack::default();
         self.name = Some(dollar0);
         self.args = positional;
         self.synthetic_pid = Some(synth);
